OL,3,GSouth West
OL,4,
OL,5,CToday:FCloudier this morning with a
OL,6,Ffew spots of rain likely, before
OL,7,Fclearing eastwards. Skies brightening
OL,8,Fup from the west by lunchtime, with
OL,9,Fplenty of sunshine developing.
OL,10,FGenerally feeling fresher than of late
OL,11,Fthough still above the May average.
OL,12,
OL,13,CTonight:FClearer skies for many
OL,14,Fovernight which will allow
OL,15,Ftemperatures to fall, giving a much
OL,16,Fmore comfortable night for many.
OL,17,FStaying dry with mist and fog in
OL,18,Fplaces.
OL,23,QppppppppppppppppppppGSource: Met Office
OL,24,ANext Page  BWeather  CReg News  FReg TV
